SIMPLE: assonant
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Assonant
<hw>As"so*nant</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>assonans</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>assonare</ets> to sound to, to
correspond to in sound; <ets>ad</ets> + <ets>sonare</ets> to sound,
<ets>sonus</ets> sound: cf. F. <ets>assonant</ets>. See
<er>Sound</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having a resemblance of
sounds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Pros.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to the peculiar
species of rhyme called <xex>assonance</xex>; not consonant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Assonantal</ent>⟦br⟧
